'Sweden' ( ; ), officially the 'Kingdom of Sweden' (Swedish: ), is a
Scandinavian country in Northern Europe. Sweden borders Norway and Finland, and
is connected to Denmark by a bridge-tunnel across the Ãresund.

At , Sweden is the third-largest country in the European Union by area, with a
total population of about 9.5 million. Sweden has a
low population density of with the population mostly concentrated to the
southern half of the country. About 85% of the population live in urban
areas. Yearbook of Housing and Building Statistics
2007 Sweden's capital city is Stockholm, which is also the largest city.
